# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Portal (Next.js frontend) — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and adjust ONLY if your setup
# differs from the defaults. Both variables have built-in fallbacks,
# so for standard LOCAL development you do NOT need a .env file at all.
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# Notes:
# - Only NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are read by this app. They are PUBLIC:
#   their values are inlined into the client bundle, so never put
#   secrets here. Backend secrets live in `server/.env`.
# - Real env files (.env, .env.local, ...) are gitignored; only this
#   .env.example is committed.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base URL of the backend API (note the trailing `/api`).
# Code fallback if unset: http://localhost:5000/api
#
#   LOCAL:  http://localhost:5000/api        (matches the Express server on port 5000)
#   PROD:   https://api.yourdomain.com/api    (your deployed backend URL)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# Public URL where this frontend is served. Used to build absolute
# canonical URLs in app/sitemap.ts.
# Code fallback if unset: http://localhost:3000
#
#   LOCAL:  http://localhost:3000
#   PROD:   https://www.yourdomain.com         (your deployed frontend domain)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRODUCTION CHECKLIST
# 1. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL to the real backend URL (https, includes /api).
# 2. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to the real frontend domain (correct sitemap).
# 3. On Vercel/host: add both as Environment Variables for the project
#    (Production + Preview), then redeploy — NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are
#    baked in at BUILD time, so changing them requires a rebuild.
# 4. Ensure the backend's CORS allows this frontend's origin
#    (server uses FRONTEND_URL — see server/.env).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
